<p> 
</p>
<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session  
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251</b> 
<b>OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Reports of mechanisms and mandates:  draft resolution proposed  
by the President 
</b></p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p> 1. <i>Recalls</i> its decision 1/102 of 30 June 2006 in which it decided to extend 
exceptionally for one year, subject to the review to be undertaken by the Council in conformity 
with General Assembly resolution 60/251 of 15 March 2006, the mandates and the mandate 
holders of all the special procedures of the Commission on Human Rights of the 
Sub-Commission on the Promotion and Protection of Human Rights as well as the procedure 
established in accordance with Economic and Social Council resolution 1503 (XLVIII) 
of 27 May 1970 (1503 procedure); 
</p>
<p> 2. <i>Also</i> <i>recalls</i> its decisions 1/104 of 30 June 2006 on implementation of paragraph 6 
of the General Assembly resolution 60/251 and 1/105 of 30 June 2006 on a draft framework for a 
programme of work of the Council for the first year; 
</p>
<p> 3. <i>Takes note </i>of all the reports presented at its second session; 
</p>
<p>GE.06-14421  (E)    041006 </p>

 <p> 
</p>
<p> 4. <i>Notes </i>the substantive interactive dialogue with special procedures mandate 
holders as well as with the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights; 
</p>
<p> 5. <i>Invites</i> the Secretary-General, the High Commissioner for Human Rights, the 
Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights and the Secretariat to 
continue to carry out their activities under relevant resolutions, decisions and Chairperson&#8217;s 
statements adopted by the Commission on Human Rights and to update the relevant reports and 
studies; 
</p>
<p> 6. <i>Decides</i>: 
</p>
<p> (<i>a</i>) To transmit the views of the Sub-Commission on the Promotion and Protection 
of Human Rights on the Human Rights Council&#8217;s future expert advice mechanism 
(see A/HRC/2/2-A/HRC/Sub.1/58/36) to the Working Group established pursuant to Council 
decision 1/104; 
</p>
<p> (<i>b</i>) To endorse the draft decisions transmitted by the Sub-Commission pertaining to 
current activities, with a view to allowing their continuation in accordance with Council 
decision 1/102. 
</p>
<p>----- </p>

